---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — AptusFIT"
  description="AptusFIT Privacy Policy: how we collect, use, and protect your personal data."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen flex flex-col bg-background">
    <div class="flex-1 max-w-[800px] mx-auto w-full px-5 py-16">
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors mb-10">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        Back to home
      </a>

      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-foreground mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-10">Last updated: May 18, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose-content space-y-8 text-foreground">

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Welcome to AptusFIT.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">This Privacy Policy explains how AptusFIT Pte. Ltd. ("AptusFIT", "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, stores, shares, and protects your information when you use the AptusFIT mobile application, website, and related services available through <a href="https://www.aptusfit.ai" class="text-accent hover:text-accent/80 underline">www.aptusfit.ai</a> (collectively, the "Service").</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">AptusFIT is a Singapore-registered company (UEN: 202547602D).</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">By using the Service, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">We collect information you provide directly to us, information collected automatically through your use of the Service, and information from optional third-party integrations.</p>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">A. Account Information</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">When you create an account, we may collect:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            <li>Name or display name</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Login credentials</li>
            <li>Language and regional preferences</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">B. Fitness & Profile Information</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">You may choose to provide:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Fitness goals and preferences</li>
            <li>Workout frequency and experience level</li>
            <li>Height, weight, age, and related body metrics</li>
            <li>Injury, limitation, recovery, or accessibility preferences</li>
            <li>Equipment and gym profile preferences</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">Providing this information is generally optional, but some features may function differently without it.</p>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">C. Workout & Training Data</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">We collect data generated through your use of the Service, including:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            <li>Workout history</li>
            <li>Exercises completed</li>
            <li>Sets, reps, weights, duration, and performance metrics</li>
            <li>Session feedback and training preferences</li>
            <li>Plan modifications, swaps, and training progression data</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">D. Health & Wearable Data</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">If you choose to connect Apple HealthKit, Google Health Connect, or other supported wearable/device platforms, we may access certain health and activity information you authorize, including:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Steps</li>
            <li>Calories burned</li>
            <li>Heart rate</li>
            <li>Workout sessions</li>
            <li>Activity duration and movement data</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">Health and wearable integrations are always optional and permission-based. You may revoke access at any time through your device settings.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">We do not sell health or wearable data. We do not use health or wearable data obtained through Apple HealthKit, Google Health Connect, or similar platforms for advertising, marketing, or data-broker purposes.</p>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">E. Device & Technical Information</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">We may automatically collect:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            <li>Device type and model</li>
            <li>Operating system and version</li>
            <li>App version</li>
            <li>IP address</li>
            <li>Unique device identifiers</li>
            <li>Crash logs and diagnostics</li>
            <li>Performance and reliability metrics</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">F. Usage & Analytics Information</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">We collect analytics and usage information such as:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Feature interactions</li>
            <li>Session duration</li>
            <li>Navigation flows</li>
            <li>Screens viewed</li>
            <li>General engagement patterns</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">This information helps us improve usability, reliability, and product performance.</p>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">G. Sensitive Personal Information</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Certain information you choose to provide — including injury information, wellness details, heart rate data, activity metrics, body measurements, and wearable data — may be considered sensitive personal information or sensitive personal data under applicable laws in certain jurisdictions.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">We process such information only as necessary to provide and improve the Service, support fitness and wellness functionality, personalize recommendations, and operate authorized integrations.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We use your information to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Provide, operate, maintain, and improve the Service</li>
            <li>Generate and personalize workout plans, recommendations, and AI-powered coaching experiences</li>
            <li>Adapt workouts and training suggestions based on your preferences, goals, and activity history</li>
            <li>Sync and display wearable and health-related activity data</li>
            <li>Respond to support requests and customer inquiries</li>
            <li>Send service-related notifications, reminders, updates, and account communications</li>
            <li>Monitor app reliability, security, fraud prevention, and abuse detection</li>
            <li>Conduct analytics, research, and product improvement</li>
            <li>Comply with legal and regulatory obligations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">We may also use aggregated or de-identified data for analytics, research, benchmarking, and service improvement purposes. You may opt out of promotional or marketing communications at any time, though we may still send important service-related, security, billing, or account communications.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">4. AI & Automated Recommendations</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">AptusFIT uses artificial intelligence and automated systems to generate fitness recommendations, workout plans, exercise suggestions, coaching interactions, and related training insights.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">These recommendations are generated algorithmically based on the information available to the system and may not always be accurate, complete, or appropriate for every individual or situation.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">AI-generated recommendations are intended for general fitness and wellness purposes only and are not medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">Users should exercise independent judgment and consult a qualified medical professional before beginning or modifying any exercise, training, nutrition, rehabilitation, or wellness program.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">Some AI functionality may involve processing pseudonymized or anonymized workout and usage data through third-party AI infrastructure providers.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">The Service is not intended for emergency or urgent medical use. If you believe you are experiencing a medical emergency, contact emergency services or a qualified healthcare provider immediately.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">5. How We Share Information</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">We do not sell your personal information.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We may share information in the following circumstances:</p>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">A. Service Providers</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">We may share information with trusted third-party vendors that support:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Cloud hosting and infrastructure</li>
            <li>Analytics and diagnostics</li>
            <li>Customer support</li>
            <li>Communications and notifications</li>
            <li>Authentication and security services</li>
            <li>Payment processing</li>
            <li>AI and machine-learning infrastructure</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">These providers are contractually required to protect your information.</p>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">B. AI & Infrastructure Providers</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">Certain training, workout, or usage data may be processed through third-party AI systems or cloud infrastructure providers to support AptusFIT functionality.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4">Where possible, data is anonymized or pseudonymized before processing.</p>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">C. Legal Compliance</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">We may disclose information if required to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            <li>Comply with applicable law or legal process</li>
            <li>Protect rights, safety, or security</li>
            <li>Detect fraud, abuse, or unauthorized activity</li>
            <li>Enforce our Terms of Service</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">D. Business Transfers</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">If AptusFIT is involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, restructuring, or sale of assets, user information may be transferred as part of that transaction subject to standard confidentiality and data protection obligations.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">6. International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">Your information may be transferred to, processed in, or stored in countries outside your country of residence, including Singapore and jurisdictions where our service providers or infrastructure partners operate.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">By using the Service, you acknowledge that data protection laws in those jurisdictions may differ from those in your country of residence.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Where required, we take reasonable measures intended to protect personal information during international transfers.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We retain personal information for as long as reasonably necessary to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Provide the Service</li>
            <li>Maintain account functionality</li>
            <li>Comply with legal, tax, accounting, security, or regulatory obligations</li>
            <li>Resolve disputes and enforce agreements</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">You may request deletion of your account and associated personal information by contacting us at <a href="mailto:Contact@AptusFIT.ai" class="text-accent hover:text-accent/80 underline">Contact@AptusFIT.ai</a>.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We will process deletion requests within a reasonable timeframe, generally within 30 days unless a longer retention period is required by law or legitimate operational necessity.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-2">Please note that:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Certain backups, logs, and archived copies may temporarily persist after deletion</li>
            <li>Some information may be retained for fraud prevention, security, legal compliance, or dispute resolution purposes</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">8. Data Security</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We implement commercially reasonable technical, administrative, and organizational safeguards designed to protect your information, including:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Encrypted data transmission</li>
            <li>Access controls</li>
            <li>Authentication protections</li>
            <li>Secure infrastructure providers</li>
            <li>Internal security monitoring</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">However, no internet transmission or electronic storage system can be guaranteed to be completely secure.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your login credentials and for notifying us immediately of any suspected unauthorized account access.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">9. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights under applicable privacy laws, including the Singapore Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA), the European Union General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA/CPRA).</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">These rights may include:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Accessing personal information we hold about you</li>
            <li>Correcting inaccurate information</li>
            <li>Requesting deletion of your information</li>
            <li>Restricting or objecting to certain processing</li>
            <li>Requesting portability of your information</li>
            <li>Withdrawing consent where processing is consent-based</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">Please note that withdrawing consent for certain data processing activities may limit or disable some features of the Service, including AI personalization, workout recommendations, wearable integrations, reminders, or account functionality.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:Contact@AptusFIT.ai" class="text-accent hover:text-accent/80 underline">Contact@AptusFIT.ai</a>. We may need to verify your identity before processing certain requests.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">10. Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">Our website and related services may use cookies, SDKs, analytics tools, and similar technologies to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Maintain functionality</li>
            <li>Understand usage trends</li>
            <li>Improve performance</li>
            <li>Support authentication and security</li>
            <li>Measure engagement and reliability</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">You may control certain cookie preferences through your browser or device settings.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Disabling some technologies may impact portions of the Service.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">11. Payments & Subscriptions</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">Certain paid features or subscriptions may be processed through third-party payment providers, including Apple App Store, Google Play, or other authorized payment processors.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">AptusFIT does not store full payment card information on its own servers.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Payment processing is governed by the applicable third-party payment provider's privacy policies and terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">12. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">The Service is not directed to children under the age of 13 (or the minimum legal age required in your jurisdiction).</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We do not knowingly collect personal information from children without appropriate legal consent.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">If you believe a child has provided us with personal information in violation of this Policy, please contact us and we will take reasonable steps to delete the information.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">13. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">If we make material changes, we may notify users by:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date</li>
            <li>Posting a notice within the Service</li>
            <li>Sending email or in-app notifications where appropriate</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Your continued use of the Service after updates become effective constitutes acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">14. Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">If you have questions, concerns, or privacy-related requests, please contact:</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mt-3">
            AptusFIT Pte. Ltd.<br />
            Singapore (UEN: 202547602D)<br />
            Email: <a href="mailto:Contact@AptusFIT.ai" class="text-accent hover:text-accent/80 underline">Contact@AptusFIT.ai</a>
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="py-10 border-t border-border bg-background">
      <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-5">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4">
          <p class="text-sm m-0">
            <a href="mailto:Contact@AptusFIT.ai" class="text-accent hover:text-accent/80 transition-colors underline font-medium">
              Contact Us
            </a>
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            <a href="/policy" class="hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a>
            <span>·</span>
            <a href="/terms" class="hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Terms of Service</a>
          </div>
          <p class="text-center text-sm text-muted-foreground m-0">
            © 2026 AptusFIT Pte. Ltd. a Singapore Registered Company with Registration No. 202547602D
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Base>
